lattice3dnlshell_dmg_bend_n7.out
Shell-mode lattice3dnl (large rotations), latticedamage, hybrid layered (N=7): pure out-of-plane bending. Tension-face cracking propagates through-thickness under the large-rotation kinematics. Regression check on the layered damage path through the geometric-nonlinear element.
StaticStructural nsteps 100 rtolv 1.e-6 ddm 2 2 5 ddv 1 1.e-2 ddltf 2 nmodules 1
errorcheck
domain 3dLattice
OutputManager tstep_all dofman_all element_all
ndofman 2 nelem 1 ncrosssect 1 nmat 1 nbc 1 nic 0 nltf 2
node 1 coords 3 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 bc 6 1 1 1 1 1 1
node 2 coords 3 1.000000e-01 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 bc 6 1 1 0 1 0 1
lattice3Dnl 1 nodes 2 1 2 crossSect 1 mat 1 shellnormal 3 0.0 0.0 1.0 polycoords 12 0.05 -0.05 -0.005   0.05 0.05 -0.005   0.05 0.05 0.005   0.05 -0.05 0.005
latticecs 1 material 1 nlayers 7
latticedamage 1 d 2400. talpha 0.0 e 30.e9 e0 1.e-4 wf 1.e-4 a1 0.5 a2 1.0
BoundaryCondition 1 loadTimeFunction 1 prescribedvalue 0.0
ConstantFunction 1 f(t) 1.
PiecewiseLinFunction 2 nPoints 2 t 2 0. 100. f(t) 2 0. 1.
#%BEGIN_CHECK% tolerance 1.e-2
## Same setup as lattice3dshell_dmg_bend_n7.in but with lattice3Dnl (large-rotation
## element). At small rotation (step 10) the values match the small-rotation
## twin exactly; from step 25 onward they diverge progressively as the geometric
## nonlinearity in the rotated rigid arm starts to bite.
#REACTION tStep 10  number 1 dof 5 value -2.5000e+00
#REACTION tStep 25  number 1 dof 5 value -6.0707e+00
#REACTION tStep 50  number 1 dof 5 value -9.3365e+00
#REACTION tStep 100 number 1 dof 5 value -1.4305e+01
#%END_CHECK%
